> Wouldn't it be nice if there were some mathematical process which
> would apply to ciphering which would automatically develop all
> possible attacks, and their related strengths?

Well, yeah, it would be nice, but given that we haven't even
been able to resolve whether or not P = NP this doesn't seem
likely any time soon.  Until we have a strong enough foundation
to base such formal security claims on we just need to do the
best we can...

